(1188, '2010-10-20 03:33:03', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, '', 2011, 'Student programming samples will be collected.', 'Students in CSC 160 during winter term, CSC 306 and CSC 495 in spring term.', 'Approximately 60 students', 'Winter term and Spring term', 'None', 'We will be evaluating the procedural design and programming skills of the samples using a rubric the department crafted.  This rubric measures three main areas of procedural design and procedural programming.  Each sample will be scored on a scale of 0-3. The samples will be averaged according to the student''s program BA/BS/minor/other.', 'The instructor of CSC 160 (Judy Walters), the instructor of CSC 306 (Steve Renk), and the instructor of CSC 495 (Caroline St.Clair).', 'Each sample will be reviewed by two faculty.  Scores will be averaged for each class/program.\r\nA comparison will be made among the results of the three courses.  We expect to students in 495 to achieve an average score of 2.1-3.0, for students in 306 to achieve 1.1 - 2.0 and for students in 160 to achieve 0.1 - 1.0. The entire department will review the results.', 'No', '', '2', '2'),
